.TH PCAN-VIEW 1 "June 2026" "pcan-view 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pcan-view \- GTK CAN / CAN FD bus monitor using Linux SocketCAN
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pcan-view
.RI [ OPTION ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pcan-view
(PCAN-View Linux, by Taksys) is a GTK3 desktop application for monitoring,
transmitting, and recording CAN and CAN FD traffic via the Linux SocketCAN
subsystem (PF_CAN).
.PP
It provides a live statistics bar, a real-time receive trace, one-shot and
cyclic message transmission, CAN FD payloads up to 64 bytes, and CSV trace
export. Missing virtual CAN interfaces can be created and brought up
automatically through a graphical authentication prompt.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a short usage summary and exit.
.PP
With no options, the graphical application is launched.
.SH USAGE
Start the application and choose
.B File > Connect
(or press
.BR F5 )
to open the connection dialog. Select an interface (for example
.BR vcan0 ),
the nominal bit rate, and optionally CAN FD, then connect. Use the
.B Trace
menu to record traffic and export it as CSV.
.SH "VIRTUAL CAN TESTING"
To test without hardware:
.PP
.nf
    sudo modprobe vcan
    sudo ip link add dev vcan0 type vcan
    sudo ip link set up vcan0
    cansend vcan0 123#DEADBEEF
.fi
